text.paragraph:
Pregnancy Category D (See 
                              WARNINGS
                           )

Skin: Toxic epidermal necrolysis (TEN) and Stevens-Johnson syndrome (SJS) (see 
   BOXED WARNING
), pruritic and erythematous rashes, urticaria, , photosensitivity reactions, alterations in skin pigmentation, exfoliative dermatitis, erythema multiforme and nodosum, purpura, aggravation of disseminated lupus erythematosus, alopecia, and diaphoresis. In certain cases, discontinuation of therapy may be necessary. Isolated cases of hirsutism have been reported, but a causal relationship is not clear.

Metabolism: Fever and chills, inappropriate antidiuretic hormone (ADH) secretion syndrome has been reported. Cases of frank water intoxication, with decreased serum sodium (hyponatremia) and confusion have been reported in association with carbamazepine use (see 
   PRECAUTIONS, Laboratory Tests
). Decreased levels of plasma calcium have been reported.
